@node intro "Introduction"

AminetGetFTP is a program, that let's you get the Aminet Recent
Uploads in the Aminet Recent Mail with AmFTP. You can choose the 
recent mail by hand or let AminetGetFTP scan our whole folder for
recent mails. After that you can select the uploads you want, you
click on the start button, AminetGetFTP runs Miami and goes online,
and runs AmFTP and gets the files. When the files are on your HD 
AminetGetFTP goes offline and extracts the received archive to a 
place of your choice (just if you wish). It is very configureable,  
very user-friendly and has many features.

@endnode

@node feat "Features" 

Features of AminetGetFTP are:

- TritonGUI
- downloads files very fast
- comfortable Configprogram
- you can select a predefined aminet site or specify a own server address
- easy to use
- no limit how much files you want to get
- you have two lists, in the upper you can select which upload you want,
  and in the lower are the uploads, that you want, displayed and can
  be removed everytime.
- you can store files you want to get on disk, collect them and get them
  all at once at a later time
- PropFonts
- you can use your own fonts
- if you click on "Get the files" and you are not online, AminetGetFTP
  will run Miami and go online
- progressbar that shows you what AmFTP and AminetGetFTP is currently doing
- simple but powerful
- you can open it on a pubscreen
- if you wish it goes offline automatically after the uploads are on your HD
- you can configure AminetGetFTP to execute a command or script before
  it goes offline (e.g. when you have a account at Monolith you can dismount
  your host before AminetGetFTP advices Miami to go offline)
- if you want, AminetGetFTP extracts your received archive to a directory
  of your choice
- MultiMail, when you have MultiMail enabled, then AminetGetFTP scans on its
  start your current YAM folder for recent mails and you can then select the
  recent mail by Next Mail/Last Mail buttons, the date of the recent mail
  is also displayed, when you disable it then you have to choose one recent
  mail before you run AminetGetFTP  
- I DON'T WANT MONEY FROM YOU FOR THIS! (but if you still want to send
  me some money, I won't stop you from doing so ;-))

@endnode

@node req "Requirements"

You will need:

- Miami
- YAM
- AmFTP
- RexxMast running
- a subscribtion to the "Todays recent aminet uploads" or "Weekly recent 
  aminet uploads" list. If you are not already subscribed then send a mail 
  to "listproc@mail.wustl.edu" and in the body "SUBSCRIBE aminet-daily 
  <your emailaddress>" for the daily list or "SUBSCRIBE aminet-weekly
  <your emailaddress>" for the weekly list. You will then get every day 
  or every week a list with all aminet uploads. Cool, isn't it?
- rexxreqtools.library  (available on aminet)
- rexxtricks.library (available on aminet)
- tritonrexx.library (included)
- triton.library (available on aminet)
- rexxapp.library (included)

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

Copy AminetGetFTP, the config program and the register program
wherever you want.

Copy everything from libs/ into your libs: dir and I suggest
that you make an entry for AminetGetFTP in the YAM Rexx menu.
But when you do so, YAM must not wait until AminetGetFTP
is done there is a checkbox that says "Wait until termination" or
something like this, this checkbox must not be checked and the
checkbox "Open console window" must not be checked too!
AminetGetFTP must be called as DOS command and not as rexx script!

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

Run AminetGetFTPConfig.

Explaination of the gui:


   Essential:

      Aminet site: Choose here the aminet site, from where you
                   want to get the files. Select a site
                   or select "-- Other --". If you select "Other", 
                   the "Serveraddress:" field will be enabled.

      Serveraddress: When you have selected "Other", you can type
                     in the address of an aminet site.

      AmFTP: Type in or select the AmFTP executeable by clicking 
             on the GetFile button.
   
      Save downloads to: Type in or select the directory, where all
                         downloaded uploads are saved to.


   Miscellanous:

      Get .readme: Check this box if you want to receive the readme files of
                   the uploads.

      Iconify AmFTP: Check this box if you want to iconify AmFTP while
                     AminetGetFTP is working with it.
 
      Multi mails: Check this box to enable MultiMail. If you enable it
                   AminetGetFTP will scan your actual YAM folder for 
                   recent mails. You can then choose between the serveral
                   mails in the AminetGetFTP GUI with the Next Mail/Last
                   Mail buttons. You can use then more than one recent 
                   mail in AminetGetFTP. The date of the recent mail is
                   then displayed in the "Maildate:" field in the 
                   AminetGetFTP GUI. 
                   If you don't check the Multi Mails checkbox you have
                   to choose the recent mail in YAM before you start
                   AminetGetFTP. You can then use only one recent mail. 

      Pubscreen:  Type in here the name of a pubscreen where AminetGetFTP
                  opens its windows on. If this screen does not exists 
                  when you run AminetGetFTP it will open its window on
                  the default screen (Workbench screen). 
                  
                  @{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub} Never leave this field blank!
         
                   
   Fonts:
   
      Fontname: Type in the name of the font you want to use in AminetGetFTP.

      Fontsize: Type in the size of the font you want to use in AminetGetFTP.

      Change fonts: Opens a font requester. Choose the font you want to use
                    with AminetGetFTP.


   Offline:

      Execute command before offline: 

                When you have checked the checkbox "Go Offline" in the 
                AminetGetFTP window and you check this checkbox, then 
                the field "Command:" will be enabled. Type in the command
                field a command or script to execute before AminetGetFTP
                advices Miami to go offline. For example if you have a
                account at Monolith Internet Services you can type in the
                command field the command to update or dismount your 
                hostname at Monolith. 

      Command: Type in here the command to execute before AminetGetFTP
               advices Miami to go offline (see above). 
               
               This field is only enabled when you have checked the
               "Execute command before offline" checkbox.                  

      Auto extract archive:

               Check this checkbox if you want that AminetGetFTP extracts
               the received uploads (archive) automatically.

      Extract to: Type in here the directory where AminetGetFTP should
                  extract the received archive to.

                  This field is only enabled if the "Auto extract archive"
                  checkbox is checked.
                  

Click on save to save the settings to S:AminetGetFTP.config or on
cancel to quit without saving.

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

Start YAM.

If you have MultiMail disabled select the recent mail in YAM and start
AminetGetFTP. 
If you have MultiMail enabled, then select in YAM the folder where you
have stored your recent mails and start AminetGetFTP. It will scan your
actual folder for recent mails.

The main GUI should open.


Explaination:


   Uploads: Here are the uploads displayed, click on the uploads
              you want to get. When you click on a upload, it will
              be displayed in the "I would like to get:" list.


   I would like to get: Here are the uploads displayed, that you
                          want to get. Click on an upload to remove
                          it from the list.


   Next Mail: If you have Multi Mail enabled, then click on this
              button to load the next recent mail, the uploads in
              it will be displayed in the Uploads list, and the 
              Maildate field will display the date of the current
              recent mail. This button will be disabled if you have
              disabled Multi Mail or if there is no next recent mail. 


   Last Mail: If you have Multi Mail enabled, then click on this
              button to load the last recent mail, the uploads in
              it will be displayed in the Uploads list, and the 
              Maildate field will display the date of the current
              recent mail. This button will be disabled if you have
              disabled Multi Mail or if there is no last recent mail. 


   Maildate: This field will show you the date of the recent mail, 
             when you click on the next/last buttons it will change.
             It works too with Multi Mail disabled.


   Files stored: If you have stored files with the "Store files" button,
                 then this field will show "Yes", otherwise
                 "No".


   Go Offline: Check this box if you want that AminetGetFTP goes offline
               automatically after it has received the uploads.


   Store files: This function saves the entries in the "I would like to get"
                list to YAM:AGetFTP-Stored. This is usefull if you are to
                busy to get the files now, or you want to collect files and
                get them all at once.


   Get stored: Gets the files that you have stored.


   Stored list: Opens a window that shows you all files that you have
                stored. You can remove stored uploads by clicking on
                them in the listview. Click on "Save" to save the list
                again or on "Cancel".   
                While this window is opened the main window is locked. 


   Clear stored: Deletes the stored file.

   
   @{b}NOTE: The Get stored/Stored list/Clear stored buttons are disabled
         as long as you don't have files stored!@{ub}

   Get the files: Starts AmFTP and gets the files.

   Cancel: Cancel and quit the program.


After you have clicked on "Get the files" AminetGetFTP checks for Miami.
If Miami is not running, it starts Miami and goes online. Then it starts
AmFTP and gets the files. A progressbar opens and shows you what AminetGetFTP,
or better AmFTP, is currently doing. 

If you have checked the Go Offline checkbox AminetGetFTP will go offline when
all files are received, if you have selected "Execute command before offline"
in the config program AminetGetFTP will execute your selected command before
it advices Miami to go offline.

If you selected to automatically extract the archive in the config program, 
then AminetGetFTP will extract the received archive to the dir that you have
(hopfully) selected in the config program. 

@endnode

@node reg "Registration"

At first, I don't want money from you, I just want to know that someone
uses this program. When you are a registered User, I'll mail new versions
of AminetGetFTP to you, and I will answer questions faster.
You have the full version, there are no limits for not registered users.
(I don't want to lock someone out)

If you like AminetGetFTP, please register.

For easy registering I have written a register program.

Start YAM (for making the registration mail).

Start RegisterAminetGetFTP.

Fill out the fields, explaination down here, and click on "Register me".
RegisterAminetGetFTP will write the registration mail in YAM and you
just have to send it.

The GUI:

(* = not required, if you don't want to tell this to me, leave blank)

   Name: Your name.

   E-Mail: Your email address.

   Street: The street, including number, you live in. (*)

   City: The city you live in. (*)

   Country: The country you live in. (*)

   "How do you like it": What do you think about AminetGetFTP.
                         Range is from 1 to 6. 1 is fantastic, and
                         6 is garbage.


   "Register me": Writes the register mail to me.

   Cancel: quit.

@{b}Thanks for registering!!!@{ub}

@endnode

@node hist "Histroy"

V1.0 (16-08-1998)
   -first release

V2.0 (26-08-1998)
   - made it possible to get .readme files
   - status panel added
   - button shortcuts added
   - made it possible to store files on HD
   - you can en-/disable iconifing AmFTP
   - full control of Miami (going online/offline)
   - PropFonts support added
   - font requester added
   - added more "jump points" for the progressbar
   - added status field in the progressbar

V3.0 (11-10-1998)
   - replaced the "go offline" requester with the Go Offline 
     checkbox in the main window
   - Multi Mails added
   - turned "Stored list" into a selectable list
   - old configs are recognized in the config program 
   - added auto extracting of received archive
   - speeded up download (100% faster)
   - added Execute-a-command-before-go-offline
   - you can now open AminetGetFTP windows on a pubscreen
   - removed a bug (anyone noticed this bug?), when you selected
     some uploads and clicked on "Store files" the field 
     "Files stored" still show "No"
   - added a GUI error protection
   - AminetGetFTP checks now for YAM before it starts to
     work on the recent mail
   - turned reqtools fontrequester in the config program into
     a ASL fontrequester (looks better)
   - added Tips and Tricks section in the guide
   - bug fixed, when the "wishlist" was empty and you click on
     "Get the files", then AmFTP was startet and the script interrupted
     by a syntax error

@endnode

@node tips "Some notes and tips..."

- if you get the error that your font is to big, then choose a smaller
  font or a bigger screen (open the window on a pubscreen)

- if you get other gui errors, send me a mail

- the checkboxes "Wait for termination" and "Open Console window" in YAM
  must not be checked

- it's better you don't alter the config file by hand :-)

- if really nothing happens, send me a mail and I'll send you my
  rexxreqtools- and rexxtricks.library, because a user had a problem
  that really nothing happens, I sent him my two libs and it worked, 
  but the libs were the same versions (?)

- @{b}DO THE FOLLOWING ONLY IF I ADVICE YOU TO DO THAT:@{ub}
  @{b}This is only for ADVANCED USERS, kids don't try this at home@{ub}
  You can enable the DEBUG routine by setting the ENV variable "DEBUG"
  to "1", warning, if you run AminetGetFTP with DEBUG mode enabled, 
  the program will slow down extremly and prepare for huge con: output!!!

- Snapshoting the windows:
  This is a real trick and not so easy. I have written a short dos script
  called "SnapshotWindows." To snapshot the windows do the following: 
  1. start AminetGetFTP
  2. resize the mainwindow and/or the stored-list window
  3. quit AminetGetFTP
  4. execute the "SnapshotWindows" script, open a shell, go to the 
     AminetGetFTP dir and type in "SnapshotWindows"

  5. reboot and try if it has worked

@endnode

